Plane crashes in Michigan - report . An airplane capable of carrying 35 to 40 people crashed about 10 miles west of here Thursday afternoon after taking off from Detroit Metropolitan Airport , WWJ - Radio reported . There was no word on any injuries or where the plane was heading , the radio report said . Monroe is about 30 miles south of Detroit . Southeastern Michigan , including Detroit , was blanketed under several inches of snow that started falling Thursday morning . Local weather forecasters said visibility in the area of the crash was about three - quarters of a mile Thursday afternoon . 
